  "prompt": "Did Charles Simonyi ask before his job interview at Microsoft for a non-disclosure agreement form regarding his paperwork on Word and Excel?",
  "response": "There is no publicly available information or documented evidence indicating that Charles Simonyi specifically requested a non-disclosure agreement (NDA) before his job interview at Microsoft concerning his work on Microsoft Word and Excel. \n\nHowever, it's standard practice for large technology companies like Microsoft to require employees, especially those involved in critical projects such as Word and Excel, to sign NDAs as part of their employment agreements. These agreements help protect proprietary information, intellectual property, and sensitive project details. Given Simonyi's significant contributions to these products, it is highly likely that he adhered to Microsoft's standard confidentiality policies upon his employment.\n\nIf you're interested in more detailed insights into Charles Simonyi's career and his time at Microsoft, his book \"Microsoft\u00ae Word and Excel\u00ae\" and other interviews might provide additional context about his experiences and the practices at Microsoft during his tenure.",
